The paper presents a novel energy load forecasting methodology based on Deep Neural Networks, specifically, Long Short Term Memory (LSTM) algorithms. This work involves the application of machine learning techniques to energy management, which falls under the category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The use of LSTM algorithms for time-series forecasting is a popular research area in machine learning, which falls under the category of Machine Learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves the use of deep learning techniques, which falls under the category of Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE). The paper also involves the use of intelligent decision making, which falls under the category of Systems and Control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper involves the application of software engineering techniques to implement the proposed methodology, which falls under the category of Software Engineering (cs.SE).
